{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bbb23deb-1d7a-4340-b74f-1b8a6a4edfe2","content":"No files found in the workspace — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding:\n- `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` — imports the namespace\n- `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — enables compiled bindings against that type\n\nYour existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same — the XAML compiler now resolves them at build time instead of using reflection at runtime.\n\n**2. Catch errors at build time — enable strict mode in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Warnings on binding mismatches (default with x:DataType) -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, the compiler validates every `{Binding}` path. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` produces a **build error** (e.g., `XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"`).\n\n**3. Opt out locally when needed** (e.g., for bindings resolved only at runtime):\n\n```xml\n<!-- Disables compiled binding for this one element -->\n<Label Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" x:DataType=\"x:Null\" />\n```\n\n### Summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Enable compiled bindings | Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element |\n| Import the VM namespace | `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` |\n| Build-time error on bad paths | Automatic once `x:DataType` is set |\n| Opt out for one element | `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa0e0b92-7a35-43ea-90bf-69ce41336b66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The files don't exist yet. The user is asking me to convert their page to use compiled bindings and explain how to catch binding errors at build time. Since there are no files, I'll provide a clear explanation with the code changes needed.\n\nLet me give them the concrete conversion and explanation.","outputTokens":720,"requestId":"7FE4:51E7A:622A44B:6AEC682:69F15631"},"id":"ed08b071-3100-4dd4-94b5-7c735288c827","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:52:16.498Z","parentId":"910c350f-6643-46de-9720-f9471ccc3bfe"}
